<h2>San Jose Energy Incentives</h2>
<p>San Jose residents have access to substantial energy incentives that make solar and HVAC upgrades highly attractive. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides 30% of system costs back as a tax credit, applicable through 2032. This credit applies to solar panels, inverters, installation, and even solar batteries. California's Self-Generation Incentive Program (SGIP) offers additional rebates for battery storage systems, particularly valuable given PG&E's time-of-use rates and potential power shutoffs during fire season.</p>

