<p>Downtown San Jose's high-rise condominiums and modern developments often have shared solar options and newer HVAC systems, while East San Jose neighborhoods with smaller, older homes represent excellent opportunities for energy retrofits. The Evergreen area's newer construction typically accommodates solar installations easily, and the slightly warmer microclimate may benefit from higher-capacity cooling systems. North San Jose's tech corridor features modern homes already designed for efficiency, making solar additions straightforward and highly effective.</p>

