<p>Battery storage systems allow San Jose residents to store excess solar energy for evening use, powering HVAC systems during PG&E's expensive peak hours. Given the utility's time-of-use rates, this storage capability can double the effective value of solar energy. Many San Jose homeowners are achieving net-zero energy consumption by combining right-sized solar arrays with high-efficiency HVAC systems, effectively eliminating their electricity bills while maintaining comfortable indoor temperatures year-round.</p>

